==English==
===Etymology===
Shortened from ''Berkeley Hunt'' or ''Berkshire Hunt''
[[Cockney rhyming slang]] for '''[[cunt]]''', a disagreeable and rude person.

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɜː(r)k|-ɜː(r)k]]

===Noun===
'''berk''' (''plural'' '''berks''')

#(''British slang'') A [[fool]].
